01:10:15.200 --> 01:10:16.240
AUDIENCE: --articulate it well.

01:10:16.240 --> 01:10:18.115
WILLIAM BONVILLIAN: Or
Martin if you know it.

01:10:18.115 --> 01:10:20.180
AUDIENCE: If you know
it better [INAUDIBLE]..

01:10:20.180 --> 01:10:20.630
WILLIAM BONVILLIAN:
I don't know.

01:10:20.630 --> 01:10:21.684
We'll find out.

01:10:21.684 --> 01:10:22.590
[LAUGHTER]

01:10:22.590 --> 01:10:24.160
AUDIENCE: You do it, and
then I'll appendix anything--

01:10:24.160 --> 01:10:25.410
WILLIAM BONVILLIAN: Please do.

01:10:28.930 --> 01:10:31.630
It's an example that
Suzanne Berger uses.

01:10:31.630 --> 01:10:36.490
And the point about Zara
is that, by locating

01:10:36.490 --> 01:10:40.600
its production facilities it's
very close to its markets,

01:10:40.600 --> 01:10:47.140
it's able to move production
to its sale system

01:10:47.140 --> 01:10:49.870
in a very, very
short period of time.

01:10:49.870 --> 01:10:53.170
So by tracking fashion
markets and what

01:10:53.170 --> 01:10:55.380
appears to be
moving and selling,

01:10:55.380 --> 01:10:59.280
it's able to shift its
production system quickly

01:10:59.280 --> 01:11:02.620
onto new styles that
seem to be emerging.

01:11:02.620 --> 01:11:05.595
Whereas if you shipping
that style across, say,

01:11:05.595 --> 01:11:08.680
8,000 miles of ocean
in a container ship

01:11:08.680 --> 01:11:13.990
that's moving at 8 and 1/2
knots, you're not in the game.

01:11:13.990 --> 01:11:16.900
So Zara has figured
out how to keep

01:11:16.900 --> 01:11:21.370
that relationship between
production facility, market,

01:11:21.370 --> 01:11:25.420
and sales facility very
tight, and therefore, be

01:11:25.420 --> 01:11:27.940
able to serve emerging markets.

01:11:27.940 --> 01:11:30.040
Fashion is somewhat
different than other areas,

01:11:30.040 --> 01:11:32.230
but the point, I
think, is still there.

01:11:32.230 --> 01:11:34.780
But serve emerging
markets very quickly--

01:11:34.780 --> 01:11:36.500
so rising to your
market opportunities

01:11:36.500 --> 01:11:38.610
in very short periods of time.

